from hayne jim hayne subject re history question in article david lesher write an now-deceased prof tell u will student about a project he have work on during wwius they need a mega-power pa with very clear audio quality the purpose wa to bellow at refugee from aircraft their solution wa a giant compressed-air source and a horn with parallel shutter work by a small audio system i think he say it work very well thu the war dept cancel the project gee i get the idea from somewhere that device like thi be in common use in wwius so that commander on board ship could bellow at the troop land on a beach for example which remind me of an anecdote from the at a communication conference a marine corps communication officer say he do care much for all the spread-spectrum multi-acces expensive communication system that person be talk about at the time what he want wa a kilowatt broadcast transmitter on the ship and a japanese transistor radio stick in the ear of every marine hit the beach hayne hayne ya can talk all ya wan na but it than it wa no it aint but ya get tum know the territory meredith willson the music man 